relevant_findings.findings: Absence of subcutaneous fat on face, arms, and upper part of trunk. Livedo reticularis on legs. Erythematous alopecic area 2 cm in diameter on scalp.
relevant_findings.biopsy_results: Atrophic epidermis, vacuolar degeneration of basal layer, mild perivascular inflammatory infiltrate, and mucine deposits. Direct immunofluorescence positive.

physical_examinations.changes_over_time: In 1979, all fat on the upper half of her body had disappeared; no further details on changes over time provided.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Significant findings included anticardiolipin antibodies positive.
